dct_description_sm: Topography by H. E. Simmons, J. C. Hilliard, A. T. Munson, E. W. Gouchenour, P. L. Sampson, A. W. Thomas, and F. W. Weber. ... Topography in Indiana from chart of the Wabash River by Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army. Variant title: Carmi quadrangle, Illinois--Indiana. Filing title: Carmi, Ill.--Ind. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V763 3360 II. Polyconic projection. Washington, D.C. : Interior--Geological Survey, 1965. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows White County, Illinois, and small portion of Posey County, Indiana. Contour interval 10 feet. At head of map: State of Illinois, Department of Registration and Education, Geological Survey Division. Surveyed in 1921 and 1939-1940. "N3800--W8800/15." "AMS 3360 II-Series V763."
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers; Geological Survey (U.S.)
